The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, April 22, 2004 				 Calcutta under multimedia spell
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, April 21: The city is set to become the hub of animation and multimedia training with a second centre starting courses in June, this time with international collaboration.																								Calcutta-based Netguru has signed a memorandum of understanding with Multimedia University (MMU), a Malaysian institute, to offer an advanced diploma in creative multimedia.																								We will be the master franchisee for Multimedia University in India, said S Bhanja, chief operating officer of Netguru. The courses will offer training in multimedia, 2D and 3D animation, he added.																								MMU will be responsible for upgrading the curriculum, conducting entrance examinations and honing the aesthetic and creative skills, said Ahmad Rafi Mohamed Eshaq, dean of the faculty of creative multimedia, MMU.																								Students who complete the one-year course can also apply for a degree course in Malaysia. The course will cost Rs 40,000 upwards. The course is likely to begin in the first week of June with 50 students.																								MMU and Netguru also plan to form a joint venture production firm to work on overseas projects.																								A joint production house is on the anvil, said Bhanja. We will also be doing research and development on animation software.																								Netguru also plans to take the courses to the neighbouring countries of Bangladesh and Myanmar, Nepal, Bhutan and Sri Lanka. 
